    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I hope your weekend plans went well. Did you get a chance to try walking in the park while listening to some Bollywood music?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I did walk in the park on Sunday. I listened to some old Bollywood songs. Like \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\". It reminds me of my childhood. I also played cricket a bit in the evening. How about you? Did you do anything fun this weekend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds lovely! \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\" is a gem — it’s fun how music can take us back. You said it reminds you of your childhood — what part of it made you smile?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I used to sing that song with my grandfather on old cassettes. We would sing together while he drove me to school. Those memories feel warm. I think I should go now. Talk to you later."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds very special — cassettes and grandfathers make the best music memories. I’m glad you had a good walk and cricket time, too. Tell me, did you try any old songs on your own this week?"
    }
  ],
